---@class ShaderUtil @Utility functions to assist with working with shaders from the editor.
---@field ShaderHasError fun() @Checks if a shader has any compilation errors. Ignores warnings.
---@field GetMissShaderName fun() @Returns the name of a user-defined miss Shader from within a RayTracingShader.
---@field GetPassKeywords fun() @Gets the local shader keywords that are valid for a Pass within a particular shader.
---@field GetComputeShaderMessageCount fun() @Returns the number of errors and warnings generated by the Unity Shader Compiler for the given ComputeShader.
---@field GetRayGenerationShaderCount fun() @Returns the number of ray generation Shaders defined whitin a given RayTracingShader.
---@field GetRayGenerationShaderName fun() @Returns the name of a user-defined ray generation Shader from within a RayTracingShader.
---@field GetShaderMessageCount fun() @Returns the number of errors and warnings generated by the Unity Shader Compiler for the given Shader.
---@field anythingCompiling fun() @When true, the Editor is compiling some Shaders asynchronously at the point of query.
---@field ClearShaderErrors fun() @Clears compile time messages for the given shader.
---@field ShaderPropertyType ShaderUtil.ShaderPropertyType @Type of a given texture property.
---@field GetCallableShaderName fun() @Returns the name of a user-defined callable Shader from within a RayTracingShader.
---@field CreateShaderAsset fun() @Creates a new Shader object from the provided source code string. You can use this method alongside the ScriptedImporter to create custom shader generation tools in the Editor.
---@field CompilePass fun() @Request the Editor to compile the Shader Variant needed for the specific pass of the given Material.
---@field UpdateShaderAsset fun() @Replaces the existing source code in the specified shader with the source code in the supplied string.
---@field ClearShaderMessages fun() @Clear compile time messages for the given shader.
---@field GetAllShaderInfo fun() @Returns an array of ShaderInfo of all available shaders. That includes built-in shaders.
---@field GetPropertyCount fun() @Get the number of properties in Shader s.
---@field GetMissShaderCount fun() @Returns the number of miss Shaders defined whitin a given RayTracingShader.
---@field GetCurrentCustomEditor fun() @Gets the current custom editor for the shader you pass in.Depending on the render pipeline asset assigned in your Graphics Settings, the custom editor can change if the shader has a different custom editor for one or multiple render pipeline assets.
---@field GetCallableShaderCount fun() @Returns the number of callable Shaders defined whitin a given RayTracingShader.
---@field GetPropertyDescription fun() @Get the description of the shader propery at index propertyIdx of Shader s.
---@field GetShaderMessages fun() @Returns each error and warning generated by the Unity Shader Compiler for the given Shader.
---@field HasProceduralInstancing fun() @Determines whether the specified Shader contains a valid Procedural Instancing variant.
---@field GetShaderPlatformKeywordsForBuildTarget fun() @Gets the platform keywords for a shader, given a shader compiler platform, build target, and optional graphics tier. These platform keywords are necessary to properly compile a shader for a given target.
---@field SetAsyncCompilation fun() @Adds shader compilation mode command in the CommandBuffer.
---@field GetRangeLimits fun() @Get Limits for a range property at index propertyIdx of Shader s.
---@field GetRayTracingShaderMessages fun() @Returns each error and warning generated by the Shader Compiler for the given RayTracingShader.
---@field GetCustomEditorForRenderPipeline fun() @Gets the shader's custom editor class name for a specific render pipeline asset type.
---@field RestoreAsyncCompilation fun() @Restores the previous Shader compilation mode in this CommandBuffer scope.
---@field GetComputeShaderMessages fun() @Returns each error and warning generated by the Unity Shader Compiler for the given ComputeShader.
---@field RegisterShader fun() @Register a user created shader.
---@field IsShaderPropertyHidden fun() @Is the shader propery at index propertyIdx of Shader s hidden?
---@field GetPropertyType fun() @Get the ShaderProperyType of the shader propery at index propertyIdx of Shader s.
---@field PassHasKeyword fun() @Checks whether a local shader keyword is valid for a Pass within a particular shader.
---@field IsShaderPropertyNonModifiableTexureProperty fun() @Is the shader propery at index propertyIdx of Shader s a NonModifiableTextureProperty?
---@field GetRayTracingShaderMessageCount fun() @Returns the number of errors and warnings generated by the Shader Compiler for the given RayTracingShader.
---@field GetMissShaderRayPayloadSize fun() @Returns the ray payload size of a user-defined miss Shader from within a RayTracingShader.
---@field IsPassCompiled fun() @Checks if the Shader variant for the given pass in the Material has already been compiled.
---@field GetCallableShaderParamSize fun() @Returns the parameter size of a user-defined callable Shader from within a RayTracingShader.
---@field GetTexDim fun() @Gets texture dimension of a shader property.
---@field ShaderHasWarnings fun() @Checks if a shader has any compilation warnings. Ignores errors.
---@field GetShaderInfo fun() @Gets ShaderInfo for the given shader.
---@field ClearCachedData fun() @Clears all internally-cached data that was generated for the given shader, such as errors and compilation info.
---@field GetShaderData fun() @Get the shader data for a specific shader.
---@field hardwareSupportsRectRenderTexture fun() @Does the current hardware support render textues.
---@field GetPropertyName fun() @Get the name of the shader propery at index propertyIdx of Shader s.
---@field allowAsyncCompilation fun() @When true, asynchronous Shader compilation is allowed at the current call site.
